  "original_title": "\u0d89\u0db1\u0dca\u0daf\u0dd3\u0dba \u0da2\u0db1\u0dcf\u0db0\u0dd2\u0db4\u0dad\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dbb\u0dab\u0dba \u0d85\u0daf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Indian presidential election today",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Indian presidential election is scheduled to be held today (18) and the two main candidates in the presidential election are Draupadi Murmu and Yashwat Singh.",
        "Draupadi Murmu will contest the presidential election representing Prime Minister Narendra Modi's BJP-led National Democratic Alliance, while Yashwat Singh will represent opposition political groups led by the United Progressive Alliance.",
        "64-year-old Draupadi Murmu is an Indian politician as well as a teacher. She is a member of Bharatiya Janata Party. Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi has said on many occasions that she is suitable for the presidential candidacy.",
        "Draupadi Murmu was the Governor of Jharkhand from 2015 to 2021. She is a leader representing the tribal community of the Indian state of Odisha. If Murmu is elected president, she will be the first tribal woman to hold the post.",
        "Yashwan Sinha, 84, represents the Trinamool Congress. Sinha, a former BJP leader. Sinha served as the Finance Minister of India from 1990 to 1991 and from 1998 to July 2002. It was under Prime Ministers Chandra Shekhar and Atal Bihari Vajpayee.",
        "Yashwan Sinha was the Home Minister of India from 2002 to 2004.",
        "According to the Constitution of India, the President of the country is not elected by popular vote, but by the votes of the representatives of the Parliament.",
        "The counting of votes and the release of the results of the presidential election held today (18) will take place on the 21st.",
        "Although the Prime Minister has more powers, the President of India is the head of state of the Republic of India. The President is the formative leader of the Indian Executive, Legislature and Judiciary. In addition, the President is also the Commander-in-Chief of the Indian Armed Forces. The term of office of the President of India is five years.",
        "The selection of the President is done by an electoral college which includes members of the two Houses of the Parliament of the Central Government (Lok Sabha and Raj Sabha) and representatives of the State Councils.",
        "The electorate consists of members elected by popular vote of twenty-nine Indian states and representatives of the constituent assemblies of union territories."
      ],
